author: Fungi
title: Instagram works great on Kindle, so far
content: Works well, not pray for continued support on the Fire platform. My smart phone is overloaded with all the apps I can't live without, but I still wanted to keep up with friends that post on Instagram. So far Instagram has fewer "shares" and ads. I want to see what they are up too, and not get a notification every time they read something they think the work should know about (which for some people is everything they read). And Facebook on Fire does a crappy job of blocking notifications. I keep turning it off but apparently every time there is an update Facebook manages to turn it on again, and my status bar fill up with dozens if not not hundred of "Carl read some piece of crap and he thinks you will be somehow grateful that he let you know about it".  OK, so this is really a review of Facebook, but also the reasons I like Instagram more.

title: Works on my 3rd Gen Kindle Fire HDX
content: I have Instagram on my Kindle Fire HDX (3rd Gen) but the app doesn't show up in my cloud and I can't find any record of an order.  I was so perplexed by this that I used the Mayday feature to find out how it could be that I have it.  The Amazon agent was terrific and after digging around a bit she found that at some point a third party app had been downloaded to my device from a place called 1Mobile Market.  The kids must have done this at some point because I have no memory of installing a third party app.  But Instagram does work on the Kindle Fire HDX devices.  I'm not sure why we have to go through a 3rd party source to get it but I haven't had any problems with the app and it has been on my device since 2015.  I tried but it will not download to my Kindle Fire HD.

author: Fiona
title: Needs updated!
content: This app worked fine (aside from the lack of full pictures or dms) until a few days ago when it stopped working. When I try to log in, it just opens my feed for half a second before logging me out again. The lack of apps available for Amazon products is terribly frustrating, and the ones that you can find are rarely, if ever, updated, and I suspect that the lack of updates is what's causing this Instagram issue (the version I get on my Fire phone is months, if not years, behind what I see on iPhones). Amazon needs to provide a better selection of apps, and start supporting updates for the ones that they do have, or risk losing the majority of their customers to Android.

author: disgruntled user
title: does not work as promised, and now it doesn't work at all
content: I know I'm a few weeks late writing this, but the issue has yet to be fixed. Up until around 3-4 weeks ago the app worked well enough, despite missing features that are available on both ios and Android (direct messaging didn't work, and we were unable to view or post pictures that are not square framed, so if the post is in landscape view you won't be able to view the left and right edges, if it is portrait it cuts off the top and bottom). However, 3-4 weeks ago the app logged me out, and no longer allowed me to log back in, the app is literally unusable and this has yet to be fixed! Instagram still sort of works on the browser, but I can no longer post pictures and I still can't use the direct messaging.

author: Preston H.
title: Only one of its kind, that's why i use it
content: It's awful. Just awful. Facebook pits no effort into instagram at all. It's by far the most glitchy, buggy, messed up app out there. It crashes constantly (and won't let you in for a few hours sometimes), it overlaps comments a lot, it lags and says it's not connected to WiFi when it is, etc. The only reason I still use it is because a lot of stuff I do requires instagram. If you don't need to use it, then don't. (Plus they take down posts they don't like, like posts that are anti liberal a lot, peoples accounts get shut down for no reason, they don't allow "spamming" so I can't say "ok" to many times, or else it will delete my comment, make sure you don't accidentally typo your email! Because they don't let you change your email, I put a b instead of a n in my email, and it looked me out of my account and said my email was wrong so I can't use that account. And if you have a complaint, there's no way to tell anyone who works at Facebook, THEY DON'T HAVE CUSTOMER SUPPORT!) Worst. App. Ever.
